&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]] has notes on pp. 208-209 and translates on p. 208: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 [The bodhisatva] [and] likewise any divine world ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 In order to do good for the world without ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 He had given that ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 I gave [full] satisfaction to the beings. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 I was able to ... completely great mines [and] the earth. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b5 [In Vaiśāli] where I slew the worthy one. &lt;/p&gt;</item>
